      passage: `<div>The following text is adapted from Guy de Maupassant&rsquo;s 1884 story &ldquo;A Recollection&rdquo; (translated by Albert M. C. McMaster et al.). The narrator is boating down the Seine from Paris toward the countryside.<br><br>As the viaduct marking the end of Paris and the beginning of the country slipped behind us, the Seine seemed to change: no longer the crowded river of the city, it became a peaceful river of the plains.</div>`,
